Forgejo is a self-hosted lightweight software forge.

It provides Git repository hosting, issues, pull requests, wiki,
releases, packages, and optional CI integration.

This SlackBuild builds Forgejo from source.

Build requirements for Slackware 15.0 not included in the official
Slackware 15.0 tree:

  google-go-lang
  nodejs

Minimum versions required by Forgejo:

  Go >= 1.24
  Node.js >= 20 with npm

The SlackBuild checks the installed Go and Node.js versions before
building. On Slackware-current, google-go-lang and nodejs are available
in the official Slackware tree, so the SBo versions are not needed when
building on -current.

The default configuration uses SQLite. A MariaDB sample configuration is
included for production use on Slackware because MariaDB is shipped in
the official Slackware tree.

After installation, read README.SBo for runtime user creation, database
setup, LAN access, security notes, and Forgejo Actions information.
